{"key":"post-5940247","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5940247</id>\n<content>Very true.&amp;nbsp; However, as an experiment, you can put the light above and a fan blowing from right to left.&amp;nbsp; Watch what happens.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In the absence of any wind, the mushrooms grow towards the light.&amp;nbsp; You can also screw with your mushrooms if you're bored.&amp;nbsp; Every morning, rotate your trays of pinning/fruiting mushrooms by 90 degrees, and leave them until the next morning, then rotate them an additional 90 degrees.&amp;nbsp; They'll grow up in a spiral. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/smile.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:smile:&quot; title=&quot;:smile:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5940263</next>\n<prev>5940237</prev>\n<first>5940197</first>\n<last>24905092</last>\n<when>1154965386</when>\n<utime>08/07/06 06:43 PM</utime>\n</post>"}